## 15. Quick-Reference Decision Tree

```
What do you need?
│
├─ CHARACTER PORTRAIT
│  ├─ Use: Character Anchor + 5-Part Method
│  ├─ Camera: Canon EOS R5, 85mm f/1.4
│  ├─ Ratio: 2:3 portrait
│  └─ Consistency: Drift Shield for edits
│
├─ MONSTER (Horror/Realism)
│  ├─ Use: Samsung Protocol
│  ├─ Camera: Samsung Galaxy S21 Ultra / iPhone
│  ├─ Add: "boring reality, unpolished, raw"
│  └─ Lens: 16mm wide-angle from below for scale
│
├─ ENVIRONMENT
│  ├─ Use: Markdown-structured prompt
│  ├─ Dungeon: 16mm wide-angle, flash or torchlight
│  ├─ City: 200mm telephoto compression
│  ├─ Wilderness: Golden hour, volumetric fog
│  └─ Add: Foreground/midground/background layers
│
├─ BATTLEMAP
│  ├─ Use: Architect Protocol
│  ├─ "Top-down orthographic, 90-degree, no grid"
│  └─ Apply grid in VTT software
│
├─ ITEMS/LOOT
│  ├─ Single: Macro photography, f/2.8, rim light
│  ├─ Batch: 4x4 grid sprite sheet
│  └─ "No bleeding between cells"
│
├─ HANDOUT/SIGN
│  ├─ Use: OCR capability with quoted text
│  ├─ Specify font style and material
│  └─ "Text follows the curvature of the surface"
│
└─ MAGIC VFX
   ├─ Use: Physics-first principle
   ├─ Make magic the diegetic light source
   ├─ Describe physical interaction, not "glow"
   └─ VFX terminology: particles, refraction, heat haze
```

